⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The King of Adarlan
node M1 · M1 · ⟦The King of Adarlan:M1:74c707⟧

WHO   — The King of Adarlan — Conqueror of the Continent
WHAT  — The great antagonist looming over Throne of Glass — a cold and brutal sovereign who hosts a contest of killers and thieves to forge himself a personal Champion, an assassin bound to do his bidding.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — The Assassin's Blade & book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because power is the only law a conqueror answers to; because magic unchecked is a threat to a throne, and so must be driven from his realm; because a king who fears nothing still wants a weapon of his own.
HOW   — By armies and conquest, by the salt mines of Endovier and Calaculla where his enemies are worked to death, by an iron will that banned magic on pain of death — and by the contest he summons to crown a Champion.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I conquered this continent — and I will not share the power I have won.

spoken token : seik-ren-maek   ·   hex : 74c707
